description:
The brilliant and hysterical Mike Birbiglia (Sleepwalk with Me, Trainwreck) joins Anna and Sim to discuss the phenomenal success of his indie Don't Think Twice, starring Keegan-Michael Key. We also talk about Anna’s performance in Lost in Translation, dating apps, and why Mike couldn’t cast Anna in his movie. Plus, Mike turns his awkward Uber ride to Anna’s house into another hilarious improv! The gang also plays "Dealbreaker?” and there may even be an appearance by everyone's favorite Imaginarium Films executive. And don't forget to tune in tomorrow for Part 2 when we go the calls!

Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information.
